(37, 'Python Developer', '\n          <h2 class=\"mt5 t-20 t-bold mb4\">\n            About the job\n          </h2>\n\n<!---->\n<!---->        <span>\n                <p><strong>About Zelthy</strong></p><p>Zelthy (https://www.zelthy.com/) is a Healthcare Platform-as-a-Service (PaaS) solution that enables quick and secure deployment of patient care centric applications.The platform is used by global pharmaceutical companies and health-tech companies such as Bristol-Meyer-Squibb, 1mg, Cipla, DKSH, Novo Nordisk, etc to manage more than 1 million patients in 12 countries.</p><p><br>\n</p><p><strong>Requirement</strong></p><p>We are looking for a Backend Developer who has 3-5 years of experience in designing, developing and implementing backend services using Python and Django.</p><p><br>\n</p><p><strong>Opportunity:</strong></p><p>Being a part of an early team that is building a global technology product that already has traction </p><p><br>\n</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities :</strong></p><p>Contribute to the development of Zelthy Cloud Platform</p><p>1. Should be able to design and implement sufficiently large and complex features and/or architectural improvements to the product. </p><p>2. Application implementation on the Zelthy Cloud including Configuration and Customization</p><p>3. Development of Restful APIs for Zelthy core as well as for implementing Applications on the Zelthy Cloud platform</p><p>4. Perform Code and Application Lifecycle Maintenance</p><p>5. Work alongside the business team and solutioning team to design application architecture</p><p>6. Mentor Junior developers</p><p><br>\n</p><p><strong>Must Haves</strong>:</p><p>1. 3+ years of experience in designing, developing and implementing backend services using Python, Django, Django Rest Framework</p><p>2. Bachelor\'s degree in Computer Science or related technical field or equivalent work experience.</p><p>3. Understanding of software design patterns</p><p>4. Experience with Celery</p><p>5. Experience with RDBMS</p><p>6. Experience with AWS, S3, EC2, RDS, Dynamo DB, Lambda etc.</p><p>7. Proficiency in Git</p><p>8. Working knowledge of HTML/CSS and Javascript</p><p>9. Previous experience in SaaS/PaaS environment will be an advantage</p><p><br>\n</p><p><strong>At Zelthy you will get</strong></p><p><br>\n</p><p>An opportunity to be an early member of a team building a Tech Platform gaining strong global acceptance Performance-based equity and opportunity to evolve into a key leadership role within the organization. Complete lifecycle view of client accounts from acquisition to project development and deployment. Work with a performance-oriented team driven by ownership and open to experiments. Build SAAS/PAAS platform for global Pharmaceutical firms Work in Meritocracy driven, candid culture. No politics.</p><p><br>\n</p><p><strong>Benefits and Opportunity</strong></p><p><br>\n</p><p>Ours is a young team with minimal management structure. As a full-time employee of Zelthy, you will also have access to our comprehensive benefits program, which includes </p><p><br>\n</p><p>• Competitive salary </p><p>• Comprehensive health benefits</p><p>• Paid time off when you need it</p><p>• Innovative work arrangement opportunities including remote work</p><p>• Paid paternity and maternity leaves</p><p><br>\n</p><p><strong>How are our Customers using Zelthy ?</strong></p><p>1. India\'s largest oncology PAP currently managed by a Big Pharma (market cap more than 100Bn) end to end on Zelthy including patient onboarding to product tracking</p><p>2. All HIV positive patients in India are monitored by the Government through a program implemented on Zelthy (more than 1 million patients)</p><p>3. South East Asia\'s leading healthcare company with a presence in more than 12 countries has adopted Zelthy as their core technology backbone for running patient programs </p><p>4. India\'s largest ePharmacy has adopted Zelthy as the core technology powering their patient program CRMs</p><p>5. India\'s first controlled distribution network for a pharmaceutical product in India implemented launched by an Indian Big Pharma on Zelthy</p><p><br>\n</p><p><strong>Founders </strong></p><p>Anshuman Chaudhary, CEO, Zelthy (B.Tech, IIT Delhi | Ex-PwC)</p><p>Kaustubh Chandrabhan, CTO, Zelthy (B.Tech, IIT Delhi | Ex-Avendus)</p>\n<!---->        </span>\n      ', 'India', 'Zelthy', 'Shraddha Agrawal', NULL, 'General', 'https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/3244563652/?eBP=JOB_SEARCH_ORGANIC&refId=pHM0x9%2B28zXmeI68XstrUA%3D%3D&trackingId=ZyF3jFAUXx5OsnT%2BJOzbSQ%3D%3D&trk=flagship3_search_srp_jobs', 'Zelthy Cloud enables quick and secure deployment of healthcare applications. Our proprietary framework enables minimum development time and cost while ensuring that applications adhere to healthcare compliances and data security requirements.', 'https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/3244563652/?eBP=JOB_SEARCH_ORGANIC&refId=pHM0x9%2B28zXmeI68XstrUA%3D%3D&trackingId=ZyF3jFAUXx5OsnT%2BJOzbSQ%3D%3D&trk=flagship3_search_srp_jobs', 1, 0, 'naukri', '2022-08-31 20:23:09'),
